The '''Hongmaogang Cultural Park''' ({{zh|c=紅毛港文化園區|p=Hóngmáogǎng Wénhuà Yuánqū}}) is a cultural park in [[Siaogang District]], [[Kaohsiung]], [[Taiwan]]. ''[[Ang mo|Hongmao]]'' is a reference to the "red-haired" rulers of [[Dutch Formosa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://khh.travel/Article.aspx?a=6872&l=2&stype=1056&sitem=4082|title=Hongmaokang Cultural Park|publisher=}}</ref>

==History==
In 2007, the Hong Mao Gang Village was relocated from the original site in Siaogang District to make a way for [[Port of Kaohsiung|Port of Kaohsiung Intercontinental Container Terminal]]. Using a small lot of land reserved, the cultural park was established there.<ref name="autogenerated1"/>

